text: Herophila fairmairei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by James Thomson in 1857 and is found in Greece.BioLib.cz - Herophila fairmairei. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. Herophila faurmairei live 2-3 years and are 12-25 mm in length. ==References== Category:Phrissomini Category:Beetles described in 1857
